<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She makes no secret of her romance on social media. </p>

<p>And Nicole Scherzinger was again professing her love for her Brit beau Thom Evans as she took to Instagram on Sunday to share a stunning snap. </p>

<p>The Pussycat Dolls star, 42, showed off her bikini body as she cosied up to the sportsman, 35, while watching an idyllic sunset on a boat.</p>

<p>Sun-daze: Nicole Scherzinger was again professing her love for her Brit beau Thom Evans as she took to Instagram on Sunday to share a stunning snap</p>

<p>Nicole and Thom were an image of happiness as they sat on the front of the boat while looking at the flawless sunset in front of them. </p>

<p>Last week, Nicole, who is thought to be back in Los Angeles following a trip to Portugal, and her boyfriend Thom Evans posted a sweet tribute to his brother 'Maxy' in celebration of his 37th birthday.     </p>

<p>The former rugby player shared a throwback image of his older sibling and the singer during a recent meet-up to mark the special occasion.</p>

<p>'Happy Birthday Bro! Wish we could be with you to celebrate. Have a great one', the X Factor: Celebrity star penned, while musician Nicole added: 'We love you Maxy.'   </p>

<p>Going strong: Last week, Nicole, who is thought to be back in Los Angeles following a trip to Portugal, and her boyfriend Thom Evans posted a sweet tribute to his brother 'Maxy' in celebration of his 37th birthday</p>

<p>In the image, the trio appeared in great spirits as they cosied up to each other in Los Angeles. The former Castres player is currently dating Portuguese dancer Debora Casimiro after his split from Lauren Jamieson. </p>

<p>Max has won 44 caps for Scotland as a centre and wing rugby union player, and is currently without a club after being released by Castres Olympique at the end of the 2015 season. </p>

<p>According to reports, Nicole is trying for a baby with her handsome beau Thom after less than a year of dating. </p>

<p>The singer is said to be keen to start a family of her own with Thom, as the couple are looking to the future and intend on purchasing a property together in London.</p>

<p>Close-knit:  The former rugby player shared a throwback image of his older sibling and the singer during a recent meet-up to mark the special occasion</p>

<p>A friend told The Sun: 'Thom told pals he's been taking supplements to boost fertility. Nicole and Thom are ridiculously loved-up, and have had serious conversations about everything from marriage to babies. </p>

<p>'No one would be surprised if they had some baby news in the coming months.</p>

<p>'Thom currently lives with his brother and a housemate in London which hardly makes for a romantic love nest. They are looking to buy a house together once lockdown is over.'</p>

<p>Nicole's representatives declined to comment and MailOnline also contacted Thom's representatives at the time, who are yet to comment.    </p>

